      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "524193eaade876f8",
      "text": "   - CVE-2023-32409 - A WebKit flaw that could be exploited by a malicious    actor to break out of the Web Content sandbox. It was addressed with    improved bounds checks.    - CVE-2023-28204 - An out-of-bounds read issue in WebKit that could be    abused to disclose sensitive information when processing web content. It    was addressed with improved input validation.    - CVE-2023-32373 - A use-after free bug in WebKit that could lead to    arbitrary code execution when processing maliciously crafted web content."
